title: Putnam Problem Solving Session
description: We solve problems from past Putnam exams, and other difficult problems. Pizza and drinks will be provided. Hosted in collaboration with Professor Jared Weinstein.

title: What is a quasi-category?
time: HOW HAVE WE STILL NOT FINALIZED THE FUCKING TIMES IS IT 5-6 OR 6-7 OR 6:30-7:30 OR WHAT THE FUCK IS IT
description: Our club member Grant Talbert will give an introductory talk on the theory of quasi-categories, which are simplicial sets that fill inner horns. They are excellent models for (∞,1)-categories, and as such have seen significant use in recent decades in fields such as homotopy theory. In this talk, Grant will define quasi-categories, and then will explain why they are excellent models for (∞,1)-categories.
